1
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:03,163
Diane, it's 6:42 a.m.

2
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:06,125
Rough sleep.

3
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:11,130
I had dreamt I was eating a large,
tasteless gumdrop.

4
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:13,674
I awoke to realize
that I was aggressively munching

5
00:02:13,883 --> 00:02:16,802
on one of my Air-Pillow
silicone earplugs.

6
00:02:17,011 --> 00:02:19,346
Hence the tastelessness.

7
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:24,393
Perhaps I should keep a closer eye
on my after-dinner coffee consumption.

8
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:30,399
Persistent soreness in the rib area,

9
00:02:30,608 --> 00:02:34,570
which I'm treating each morning with
15 extra minutes of yogic discipline.

10
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:39,825
After which, thankfully,
the pain retreats to a cul-de-sac

11
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:43,328
in a distant suburb
of my conscious mind.

12
00:02:45,957 --> 00:02:48,542
I'm going to begin today
with a headstand.

13
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:59,094
Diane, I am now upside down.

14
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:05,767
Mind becoming porous.

15
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:12,232
The day's tasks coming into focus.
Objects growing clearer.

16
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:32,544
Diane, the Giant was right.
I did forget something.

17
00:03:37,717 --> 00:03:41,803
"I've gone north. Jack may have
the answer. Love, Audrey."

18
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:04,618
Hey. Thought we'd lost you
to the Kalispell woods.

19
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:08,914
Two retired female schoolteachers
live in that house next to the Palmers.

20
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:11,708
They have no memory
of a gray-haired man.

21
00:04:11,918 --> 00:04:14,670
I had to drink three pots
of chamomile tea to find that out.

22
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:16,171
- Hmm.
- Which reminds me.

23
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:17,798
Would you excuse me for a minute?

24
00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:19,007
- Sure.
- Thanks.

25
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:22,010
Mm. Keep looking for the
one-armed man. We gotta find him.

26
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:24,763
Excuse me, sheriff,
I just wanted to say goodbye

27
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:28,100
because, as you know,
I'm going down to Tacoma for two days

28
00:04:28,309 --> 00:04:31,228
to visit my sister Gwen
and her husband, Larry,

29
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:32,729
who had a baby last week.

30
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:35,732
- Right.
- That is, Gwen had the baby.

31
00:04:35,942 --> 00:04:39,486
Larry's the father.
You remember? It was a boy.

32
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:42,906
Well, anyway, as soon as
the Can-Do temp girl gets here,

33
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:45,826
I'll explain the phones
and the coffee and the intercom...

34
00:04:46,035 --> 00:04:47,661
- Lucy, it's okay.
- And the wag...

35
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:49,579
We got it covered.

36
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:52,207
No, she should've
been here by now.

37
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:57,713
- I can stay and at least show her...
- Lucy, don't worry. Just go.

38
00:04:58,589 --> 00:05:01,675
Sometimes the Can-Do girls can't.

39
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:06,263
- But, sheriff...
- We got it covered.

40
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:11,601
Have a safe trip, Lucy.

41
00:05:12,395 --> 00:05:13,812
Thank you.

42
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:16,064
- Morning, Coop.
- Harry.

43
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:18,025
What is the word
on our delivery tonight?

44
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:20,944
We won't need it.
We've got the jump on them.

45
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:23,655
I know where Audrey is.

46
00:05:26,868 --> 00:05:30,662
You see, the Port-O-Patient
will allow you to fluently, uh, transport

47
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:32,664
the unfortunate Mr. Johnson,

48
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:36,501
uh, allowing him to even go outside,

49
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:40,756
and sit and experience
what he can of nature.

50
00:05:40,965 --> 00:05:42,841
- Mr. Pinkle, I want my cousin Leo
- Mm-hm?

51
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:45,594
To have the fullest possible
experience of life.

52
00:05:45,803 --> 00:05:50,932
Well, that's what we're here for. Heh.
Okay, let's give it one more.

53
00:05:51,142 --> 00:05:53,268
Mr. Pinkle,
are you gonna install the ramp?

54
00:05:53,895 --> 00:05:55,812
Well, sure, of course, of course.

55
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:59,608
Uh, as a matter of fact,
I already have some...

56
00:05:59,776 --> 00:06:00,942
Some plywood ramp...

57
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:04,738
Pinewood ramp boards
that I'll install tomorrow. Absolutely.

58
00:06:04,947 --> 00:06:09,576
That's a very good suggestion.
Now, I think we are ready to go.

59
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:12,371
Finally. There we go. All right?

60
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:18,502
That's a new wrinkle.

61
