A machine is like a woman, we always
say at the machine shop. Come on.

65
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:35,394
Oh, Bobby, are you okay?

66
00:06:36,312 --> 00:06:39,398
Shelly, could you get Mr. Pinkle
a cold drink, please?

67
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:41,691
A diet soda, please.
That would be great.

68
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:43,944
Pinkle, Pinkle, Pinkle.

69
00:06:44,153 --> 00:06:47,280
This thing is a death trap.
I told you we have to keep him alive.

70
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:50,367
The insurance companies
don't exactly pay off like the slots.

71
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:51,743
After we take our cuts,

72
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:55,205
we had only money for this
or a first-rate wheelbarrow.

73
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:59,167
Oh, thank you very much.

74
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:01,920
Oh, thanks a lot.

75
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:03,880
Bobby?

76
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:12,806
- I've gotta meet Leo's lawyer.
- The hearing's today, right?

77
00:07:13,015 --> 00:07:16,101
Be just another second, folks.

78
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:19,729
Bobby...

79
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:23,150
...are we okay?

80
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:35,579
Oh, that's it.
Come and take a look. You can see it.

81
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:37,080
It works just fine.

82
00:07:38,374 --> 00:07:41,293
Come outside with me.

83
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:45,881
He can let himself out.

84
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:50,218
Bobby, we're doing real good.
Okay, that's enough. Um...

85
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:55,557
Bobby? Uh...

86
00:07:56,976 --> 00:08:01,021
Bob, Bob, I can't reach the switch.
Bobby, I've got a problem here.

87
00:08:12,241 --> 00:08:16,036
Mr. Palmer has pleaded not guilty

88
00:08:16,204 --> 00:08:18,663
to the charge
of murder in the first degree.

89
00:08:18,873 --> 00:08:21,333
The defense has requested bail.

90
00:08:21,542 --> 00:08:26,713
This pre-trial hearing is to determine
whether that bail will be granted.

91
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:29,341
Mr. Prosecutor.

92
00:08:29,884 --> 00:08:31,927
We, the people
of the State of Washington,

93
00:08:32,094 --> 00:08:35,180
move the defendant be denied bail.

94
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:37,140
On the basis of one,

95
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:40,602
the great seriousness of the crime
for which he has been accused.

96
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:45,273
Two, the apparently
premeditated nature of this act.

97
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:49,903
And three, the oft-witnessed
instability of Mr. Palmer

98
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:53,365
during the period
following the death of his daughter.

99
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:58,411
Sheriff Truman will speak
for the defense.

100
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:01,915
Your Honor,

101
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:07,045
Leland Palmer
is a well-known, well-liked,

102
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,631
well-respected member
of this community.

103
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:11,675
His roots go way back.

104
00:09:11,842 --> 00:09:14,094
His grandfather, Joshua Palmer,

105
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:17,430
brought the family here
more than 75 years ago.

106
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:22,060
Your Honor, no one can know

107
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:27,190
what it's like to lose a daughter
the way Leland did.

108
00:09:29,318 --> 00:09:30,610
That's all.

109
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:33,488
Thank you, sheriff.

110
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:36,408
Mr. Lodwick, would you care?

111
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:39,202
I thought I might sell this
to the Gazette.

112
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:42,497
They seem to like
courtroom sketches.

113
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:48,587
Yeah, why don't you try
for a little more face than that?

114
00:09:48,796 --> 00:09:50,672
High standing in the community,

115
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:53,508
and the pristine nature of his public...

116
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:54,968
Just an idea.

117
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,762
Good. Thanks, sheriff.

118
00:09:57,972 --> 00:10:02,100
The defendant is released
on his own recognizance.

119
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:04,686
Now, Leland,

120
00:10:05,813 --> 00:10:10,400
as you know,
I will require you to remain in town

121
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:14,821
and making your whereabouts
known to the sheriff

122
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:16,865
on a regular basis.

123
00:10:18,242 --> 00:10:20,910
Sid, check the calendar,

124
00:10:21,078 --> 00:10:23,747
and we'll set a date
for Mr. Palmer's trial

125
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:26,958
as soon as possible.

126
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:45,143
- Hi.
- Hi.

127
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:48,563
Thank you.

128
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:54,027
Oh, mm.

129
00:10:55,446 --> 00:10:59,699
So, what's behind those
deep blue eyes today?

130
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:02,410
I've got a proposition for you.

131
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:05,747
I'll share my life with you.
I'll tell it to you.

132
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:08,166
Part of your living novel...

133
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:12,212
...if you let me read Laura's diary.

134
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:18,093
It's intriguing.

135
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:25,600
I'll read it to you.

136
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:30,480
But it mustn't physically
leave this room.

137
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:33,858
Acceptable.

138
00:11:45,287 --> 00:11:49,374
- You'll start?
- Of course.

139
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:52,043
A bargain has been struck.

140
00:12:27,788 --> 00:12:31,374
Donna Hayward.

141
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:44,179
- Begin.
- All right.

142
00:12:44,388 --> 00:12:47,223
I'm from Twin Peaks.
Actually, I was born here.

143
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:51,644
My father delivered me.
He's a doctor.

144
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:55,523
Where are you from?

145
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:01,321
I grew up in Boston.

146
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:05,492
Well, actually, I grew up in books.

147
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:14,876
There's things
you can't get in books.

148
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:20,340
There are things
you can't get anywhere.

149
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:25,303
But we dream
they can be found in other people.

150
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:30,391
Continue.

151
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:33,311
Maybe our dreams are real.

152
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:41,778
My turn.

153
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:44,823
What are you doing?

154
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:48,493
Maybe I'll read it out here
on the lawn.

155
00:13:49,703 --> 00:13:51,454
Please.

156
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:54,791
We've only just started.

157
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,501
Why don't you come with me?

158
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:59,337
Come on.
What's there to be afraid of?

159
00:13:59,964 --> 00:14:01,464
Come on.

160
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:06,469
Please?

161
00:14:07,972 --> 00:14:09,931
Give that back to me.

162
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:22,235
Harold?

163
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,488
I'm sorry.

164
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:31,327
I'm sorry.

165
00:14:39,211 --> 00:14:41,754
The defense will continue
with its evidence.

166
00:14:41,922 --> 00:14:43,548
If you would, Mr. Racine.

167
00:14:44,174 --> 00:14:46,342
You can see from these EEGs,

168
00:14:46,510 --> 00:14:48,928
this chart here,
which is actually of my own head,

169
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:51,931
is intended to show
normal brain activity.

170
00:14:52,099 --> 00:14:54,517
Objection to the use
of the word "normal," Your Honor.

171
00:14:54,685 --> 00:14:56,269
Well, he's close enough.

172
00:14:56,604 --> 00:14:58,855
Objection overruled.

173
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:06,905
This chart here is of Mr. Johnson
and shows minimal activity.

174
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:14,162
A previously submitted
medical report

175
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:18,625
states that Mr. Johnson
has suffered diffuse brain damage.

176
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:21,544
He doesn't currently
even have the perspicacity

177
00:15:21,712 --> 00:15:24,547
to take the standard CST
competency test.

178
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:27,759
We therefore submit

179
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:31,346
that trying this individual

180
00:15:32,139 --> 00:15:34,599
would constitute a mockery
of the justice system.

181
00:15:34,975 --> 00:15:37,477
A proceeding that
the unfortunate young man

182
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:40,355
would not even faintly comprehend.

183
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:47,111
Mr. Prosecutor.

184
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:53,451
I know Leo Johnson
isn't in very good shape.

185
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:57,455
On the surface, it might seem
ridiculous to make him stand trial.

186
00:15:57,623 --> 00:16:01,501
But the trial does more
than just punish the wrongdoer.

187
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:06,005
It also brings a feeling of justice
and retribution to a community.

188
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:09,384
Among the various crimes
Leo Johnson is suspected of,

189
00:16:09,593 --> 00:16:15,181
the murder of Laura Palmer is the sort
that can wound an entire town.

190
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:17,976
As long as Leo Johnson
carries a breath,

191
00:16:18,143 --> 00:16:20,645
- All right.
- he is as eminently deserving of a trial

192
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:23,356
as this community is
of a sense of resolution!

193
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:25,400
All right.

194
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:28,695
Now, have a seat, Mr. Lodwick.

195
00:16:32,908 --> 00:16:35,326
Now, you fellas
can catch your breath.

196
00:16:36,286 --> 00:16:39,747
I, uh, am going to need to deliberate.

197
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:44,293
Mr. Cooper, Sheriff Truman,

198
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:47,171
if I could have the pleasure
of your company.

199
00:16:49,508 --> 00:16:53,594
Sid, can you fix us up with three
black Yukon sucker punches?

200
00:16:53,804 --> 00:16:55,555
Yes, Your Honor.

201
00:16:55,764 --> 00:17:00,643
Lodwick really planted his feet
and looked it in the eye.

202
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:04,772
I didn't expect him to press
on the murder charge.

203
00:17:04,940 --> 00:17:08,317
Cooper, is Leo Johnson our man?

204
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:10,737
No, sir. I don't believe he is.

205
00:17:10,904 --> 00:17:14,949
Harry, what's the temperature
of the town?

206
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:18,327
Do they want a trial or a lynching?

207
00:17:18,495 --> 00:17:21,414
They want the right man
brought to justice.

208
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:23,958
Well, they don't need a circus.

209
00:17:24,126 --> 00:17:26,544
And this poor bastard,

210
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:28,963
he seems to be a heady cabbage.

211
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,299
Thoughts, Cooper?

212
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:35,011
I feel the killer
will eventually be apprehended.

213
00:17:36,346 --> 00:17:40,808
You have to watch these.
They sneak up on you.

214
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:56,908
I'm gonna declare Leo Johnson

215
00:17:57,076 --> 00:18:00,369
to be not competent to stand trial.

216
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:05,124
And when medically possible,
that he be shipped home.

217
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:12,423
Harry, uh, do you wanna tell
the little lady yourself?

218
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,259
Thanks, Clinton.

219
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:22,558
- Cooper, how long you been here?
- Twelve days, sir.

220
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:25,353
- They're not gonna try him.
- No?

221
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:28,106
Leo is coming home.

222
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:32,235
I'll advise you to keep your eye
on the woods.

223
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:36,489
The woods are wondrous here...

224
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,784
...but strange.

225
00:18:40,327 --> 00:18:42,036
Thanks.

226
00:19:00,597 --> 00:19:02,974
Can I get you anything, Nadine?

227
00:19:04,309 --> 00:19:07,770
- Who are you?
- Who am I?

228
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:14,235
- You go to the high school.
- Well, yeah.

229
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:19,115
Heh. Yeah, it took me a second.
You're not in any of my classes.

230
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:21,784
Why don't you sit down, honey?
Let me get you a drink.

231
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:23,828
Oh, no, I'll get it.

232
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:28,374
Where are Mom and Dad?

233
00:19:28,917 --> 00:19:31,961
Oh, uh, out of town.

234
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:33,421
Oh.

235
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:35,548
Okay.

236
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:39,468
You're a jack and I'm a jack
And Steeplejacks are we

237
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:41,220
Wow.

238
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:44,807
Doc Hayward said
to roll with the punches.

239
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:49,061
Have you thought about maybe
taking her to see Dr. Jacoby?

240
00:19:49,271 --> 00:19:52,231
No, he's in Hawaii
recovering from that heart attack.

241
00:19:59,239 --> 00:20:01,866
It just came right off.

242
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:20,218
Mr. Tojamura is here.

243
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:22,470
Mister who?

244
00:20:27,809 --> 00:20:29,894
Excuse me. Uh...

245
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:34,315
- Do you have an appointment, Mr?
- Tojamura.

246
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:39,987
I represent Asian investment bank.

247
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:43,366
We have superior offer

248
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:47,870
for Ghostwood Project.

